  "prompt": "Which is the ancient education system in India?",
  "response": "The ancient education system in India is known as the \"Gurukul\" system. Here are some key details about this traditional method of education:\n\n1. Gurukul System:\n- Students lived with their guru (teacher) in the teacher's home\n- Education was residential and holistic\n- Learning was based on oral traditions and personal interactions\n- Emphasis on moral and spiritual development along with academic knowledge\n\n2. Key Features:\n- Guru-shishya (teacher-student) relationship was central\n- Education was free of cost\n- Learning was personalized and comprehensive\n- Students learned subjects like mathematics, science, philosophy, arts, and warfare\n\n3. Subjects Taught:\n- Vedas\n- Sanskrit\n- Mathematics\n- Astronomy\n- Philosophy\n- Scriptures\n- Martial arts\n- Music and arts\n\n4. Time Period:\n- Existed from ancient times (around 3000 BCE)\n- Continued through Vedic and post-Vedic periods\n- Prevalent until the introduction of modern education systems\n\n5. Notable Characteristics:\n- Focused on character building\n- Discipline and self-control were important\n- Students served their guru as part of their learning process\n\nThe Gurukul system is considered one of the oldest and most comprehensive educational approaches in human history.",
